## Accessibility — WCAG 2.2 AA targets

- Contrast: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text (≥18pt or 14pt bold) and non-text UI.
- Touch targets: 44×44 CSS px min (48 preferred). Spacing exception applies for inline links.
- Keyboard: every interactive element reachable; logical tab order; visible `focus-visible:ring-2`.
- Semantic HTML: real `<button>`, `<a>`, `<label>`, `<nav>`, `<main>` — not `<div>`s with click handlers.
- Images: meaningful `alt` (or `alt=""` for decorative). Always pass `width`/`height` to prevent CLS.
- State must never be conveyed by color alone — pair with icon + text.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`; gate animations behind it.

## Internationalization — next-intl v4

- Never hardcode user-facing strings. Use `useTranslations()` (client) or `getTranslations()` (server).
- All keys must exist in all three locales: `messages/en.json`, `messages/pt.json`, `messages/es.json`.
- PT-BR is the Brazilian variant — natural, native phrasing (NOT European Portuguese).
- ES is professional Latin-American Spanish.
- Routing helpers come from `@/i18n/navigation` — `Link`, `redirect`, `useRouter`. Do NOT import these from `next/navigation` in the localized app tree.
- Numbers, dates, currencies: use `useFormatter()` / `getFormatter()`; never string-concatenate locale-specific output.
- Avoid forced re-translation rebuilds: when changing a string, update the same key in all 3 files in the same commit.

## Don'ts

- Don't use placeholder names like `t('label1')`. Use semantic key paths: `dashboard.userMenu.signOut`.
- Don't ship icon-only buttons without an `aria-label`.
- Don't disable focus rings to "make it look cleaner".

See `.agents/rules/accessibility.md`, `.agents/rules/responsiveness.md`, `.agents/rules/i18n.md`.
